article.headline: Youngstown St. 31, W. Illinois 28
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. -- Brandon Summers threw two touchdown passes to lead Youngstown State past Western Illinois 31-28 during their season finale Saturday afternoon. Summers completed 12-for-19 for 208 yards for his two scores, including a 38-yard strike to Donald Jones late in the third. Things weren't all bad for Western Illinois as senior Herb Donaldson became the all-time leading rusher in the Missouri Valley conference with a 235-yard performance that had him running the ball 40 times. He also set a conference record with 23 games of 100 yards or more. But the Leathernecks (6-5, 4-4 Missouri Valley) had three costly turnovers, while the Penguins (4-8, 3-5 Missouri Valley) had none. Youngstown's Ferlando Williams ran for 84 yards on 26 attempts. The Leathernecks found themselves playing catch-up all afternoon after not answering the Penguin's touchdown in the first quarter. Dre Gibbs had two touchdowns for the Leathernecks, including two runs that tied the game -- in the second and the third.
